Package: phonActivR
Type: Package
Title: A Lightweight Interactive Activation Simulator for Modeling Cross-Linguistic
    Phonological Competition in Spoken Word Recognition
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-03-13
Authors@R: c(
    person("Yu-Cheng", "Lin", email = "yucheng.lin@utrgv.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5905-6928")),
    person("Hitomi", "Kambara", role = "aut",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-5302-1305"))
  )
Description: A pure-R implementation of a TRACE-style interactive activation model
    for generating predictions about phonological competition in spoken word
    recognition. Introduces the delta parameter, which operationalizes cross-linguistic
    prosodic processing constraints (moraic, syllabic, tonal) as temporal delays on
    sub-unit activation. Supports item-level simulation across full experimental
    stimulus sets with automatic phonological overlap computation from the TRACE
    7-feature phoneme matrix. Includes paradigm-agnostic empirical overlay functions
    for normalizing and superimposing model predictions onto time-course data from
    mouse-tracking, eye-tracking, ERP, or any paradigm producing a time-varying
    competition measure. Designed for cross-linguistic and bilingual spoken word
    recognition research.
